Ad Text:
Our client is an international defence supplier, who design, manufacture and integrate communications solutions for Australian and global customers. They are looking to bolster their systems engineering capability supporting a number of projects across the Land and Air sectors.

Individuals with experience across the entire systems engineering life-cycle (Design and Review, V&V, Test & Integration, Requirements Management) will be highly suitable.


The Role:

Enforce design, system and specifications as required.
Establishing test plans & procedures and test analysis
Implementation, integration, verification, and validation
System definition/high level, preliminary and detailed design
Provide requirements analysis and management with the use of software management tools such as; DOORs and/or UML.



Experience Required:

3-5 years' experience as a Systems Engineer or more
Engineering Degree in either of the following disciplines: Electrical, Communications, Electronics, Mechatronics, Software and/or Hardware
Experience in systems architecture, design & development, and test & evaluation.
Australian Citizenship essential; current or Reinstatable clearance ideal
Defence industry experience desirable.


Please only apply if you hold Australian Citizenship, can obtain and maintain a Defence Security Clearance and US International Traffic in Arms Regulations clearance procedures.

If you think you match the above criteria, please apply in Word format only. PDF is also accepted.

Kinexus is the leading supplier for recruitment solutions to the Australian Defence Industry bringing intelligent connections and ideas together to better our sovereign nations capabilities in the field, at sea or in the air.

All applications should include your resume as a word document.

For more information, visit our website www.kinexus.com.au or contact Lewis Landau on 0422 572 745.

Multiple Operations Data Engineers are required to support and maintain enterprise data assets across a modern cloud-based data platform. These roles play a key part in ensuring the reliability, performance, and operational stability of data services, supporting both business-as-usual (BAU) delivery and critical processing cycles.

The positions focus on operational support of data pipelines, month-end processing, and responding to data-related requests, while ensuring service level agreements (SLAs) are consistently met across the platform.


Key Responsibilities

Support and maintain data assets across cloud data lake, cloud EDW, legacy EDW, and analytics platforms
Provide Level 2/3 technical support across AWS, Control-M, Snowflake, Teradata (legacy), and ETL-based integration solutions
Support daily data delivery processes and month-end operational workloads
Develop and maintain SQL-based analytical and ETL code
Monitor and manage scheduling workflows using Control-M or similar tools
Work with file transfer solutions such as GoAnywhere or equivalent
Apply DevOps practices and tools in line with established delivery processes
Maintain system and technical documentation
Analyse, size, prioritise, and queue work items
Collaborate with data consumers, database developers, testers, and IT support teams
Drive continuous improvement in coding standards, delivery practices, and documentation, including knowledge sharing and training
Essential Skills & Experience

Strong experience with AWS data engineering services including Glue, S3, Lambda, EC2, and RDS
Proven experience designing and developing data pipelines using ETL/ELT frameworks
Hands-on experience with Snowflake (cloud EDW) and/or Teradata (on-prem EDW)
High level of programming capability, particularly in Python
Experience with Control-M orchestration, monitoring, or similar scheduling tools
Strong background in operational support and BAU environments
Desirable Experience

Infrastructure-as-code exposure using CloudFormation or Terraform
Experience with ETL tools such as DBT, Talend, Informatica, or similar
Advanced SQL capability
Exposure to SAS platforms (Base, Enterprise Guide, or SAS Viya)

This role will be offered as an initial 12 month contract + opportunity to extend.

Multiple roles are available in Sydney and Melbourne and are due to start early February 2026.

To apply please send your resume or contact Nat on 0430 292 875 or natalie@blackroc.co

Our client is a leading Defence consultancy with a national presence and will be seeking multiple Modelling and Simulation Engineers for upcoming contract opportunities, across the Maritime and Aerospace sectors.

These roles will involve Systems Modelling, Software Modelling and Simulation, and Verification & Validation (V&V).

Candidates with Defence experience and backgrounds in Mathematics, Physics, Computer Science, or Software Engineering are encouraged to apply. The required years of experience are flexible, and we welcome applications from both mid-level and senior professionals.

These positions are expected to start in February depending on candidate availability and processing timelines.

Responsibilities:

Integrate MATLAB/Simulink models into custom simulation environments (C++) and test integration outcomes.
Review simulation results, providing guidance and support tools.
Design and conduct tests to validate individual models and the overall system.
Create detailed documentation, including report writing and presenting results.
Develop new models and execute existing ones using various software tools.
Plan, integrate, and test the model integration process, including defining steps and documenting results.

Requirements:

Experience working on Defence platform systems or related applications.
Strong background in modelling and simulation, software development, or numerical analysis.
Familiarity with MATLAB/Simulink, C++, and modern simulation tools.
Understanding of Radar and Electromagnetic technologies
Experience with CUDA
Proficient in both Windows and Linux development environments.
NV1 security clearance or higher.

Please note: Recruitment for this position will resume after Jan 12th.

All applications should include your resume as a word document.

For more information, visit our website, www.kinexus.com.au or contact Ellen Hanratty on 03 9982 0303.
